column13: Methods, systems, and machine-readable mediums are disclosed for converting document fields into data element(s). The method may comprise receiving a plurality of text fields extracted from a document image and receiving a context (including a document type and document state information) associated with the document image. Rule(s) associated with the document type are obtained and used to process the text fields through a first document process associated with the document context. The first document process includes extracting data element(s) from at least a first set of the text fields. The data elements are posted to a searchable database.

column13: A pet waste management device includes a housing having upper and lower ends. The device includes a receiving bowl positioned in the housing, the bowl having an open upper end and a lower end having an outlet. A cover is situated upwardly adjacent the bowl upper end. A water outlet is positioned adjacent the bowl upper end to introduce water into the bowl. A supply line provides water to the water outlet. The device includes a first foot pedal configured to selectively allow water from the supply line to enter the bowl through the water outlet. A drain line is operatively coupled to the bowl lower end to drain contents of the bowl. The device includes a heating unit to prevent water from freezing, the heating unit including a resistive heating element and a thermostat and is in electrical communication with a power source.
column15: FOURNIER CURT R;;JANUSZEWSKI VICTORIA D;;BRADFORD TODD M;;FLANNERY JOHN
